Interface Locatable

All Known Subinterfaces:
AccessWatchpointEvent, BreakpointEvent, BreakpointRequest, ExceptionEvent, LocatableEvent, Method, MethodEntryEvent, MethodExitEvent, ModificationWatchpointEvent, MonitorContendedEnteredEvent, MonitorContendedEnterEvent, MonitorWaitedEvent, MonitorWaitEvent, StackFrame, StepEvent, WatchpointEvent
public interface Locatable

Since:
1.3

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type
    Method
    Description
    Location
    location()
    Returns the Location of this mirror, if there is executable code associated with it.

  • Method Details

    • location

      Location location()
      Returns the Location of this mirror, if there is executable code associated with it. Note that both Java programming language methods and native methods have executable code. Returns null for abstract methods, since abstract methods have no executable code.
      Returns:
      the Location of this mirror, or null if there is no executable code associated with it.
